...and making it about drug running,
you know?

84
00:05:25,679 --> 00:05:27,555
- Definitely.
- Why can't there be a movie...

85
00:05:27,722 --> 00:05:29,683
...simply about flowers?

86
00:05:30,183 --> 00:05:32,102
I guess we thought that maybe...

87
00:05:32,268 --> 00:05:35,647
...Susan Orlean and Laroche
could fall in love, and...

88
00:05:35,814 --> 00:05:39,567
Okay. But I'm saying, it's like,
I don't wanna cram in sex...

89
00:05:39,734 --> 00:05:42,779
...or guns or car chases...

90
00:05:42,946 --> 00:05:46,616
...you know,
or characters, you know...

91
00:05:46,783 --> 00:05:49,327
...learning profound life lessons.

92
00:05:49,494 --> 00:05:51,496
Or growing,
or coming to like each other...

93
00:05:51,663 --> 00:05:54,916
...or overcoming obstacles to succeed
in the end, you know? I mean...

94
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:57,627
The book isn't like that...

95
00:05:57,794 --> 00:06:01,631
...and life isn't like that.
You know, it just isn't. And...

96
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:07,012
I feel very strongly about this.

97
00:06:09,347 --> 00:06:12,225
John Laroche is a tall guy,
skinny as a stick...

98
00:06:12,392 --> 00:06:15,228
...pale-eyed,
slouch-shouldered...

99
00:06:15,395 --> 00:06:20,025
...sharply handsome, despite the fact
he's missing all his front teeth.

100
00:06:20,191 --> 00:06:23,778
I went to Florida two years ago
to write a piece for The New Yorker.

101
00:06:23,945 --> 00:06:28,033
It was after reading a small article about
a white man and three Seminole men...

102
00:06:28,241 --> 00:06:30,910
...arrested with rare orchids
they'd stolen out of a place...

103
00:06:31,077 --> 00:06:34,414
...called the Fakahatchee Strand
State Preserve.

104
00:06:37,542 --> 00:06:42,130
As natural selection works solely by
and for the good of each being...

105
00:06:43,923 --> 00:06:48,595
...all corporeal and mental endowments
will tend to progress towards perfection.

106
00:06:48,762 --> 00:06:52,766
It's interesting to contemplate
an entangled bank...

107
00:07:10,784 --> 00:07:12,952
Polyrrhiza lindenii.

108
00:07:14,371 --> 00:07:15,997
A ghost.

109
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:21,419
Cut her down, Russell.

110
00:08:04,421 --> 00:08:06,506
- Morning.
- Hey.

111
00:08:06,673 --> 00:08:09,509
May I ask you gentlemen what you
have in those pillowcases?

112
00:08:09,843 --> 00:08:12,345
Yes, sir, you absolutely may.

113
00:08:12,679 --> 00:08:15,682
- Okay, then, I'm asking.
- Well, okay, then.

114
00:08:15,849 --> 00:08:17,308
Let's see.

115
00:08:17,684 --> 00:08:21,479
We've got five kinds of bromeliad...

116
00:08:21,646 --> 00:08:25,066
...one peperomia,
nine orchid varieties.

117
00:08:26,776 --> 00:08:30,238
You know,
about 130 plants all told.

118
00:08:30,405 --> 00:08:32,741
Which my colleagues here
removed from the swamp.

119
00:08:32,907 --> 00:08:37,495
You're aware it's illegal to remove plants
or animals from state-owned land?

120
00:08:37,662 --> 00:08:39,539
Yeah, and don't forget...

121
00:08:39,706 --> 00:08:43,126
...these plants are all endangered, sir.
Every one of them.

122
00:08:43,293 --> 00:08:47,339
Well, exactly. That's exactly the issue.
This is a state preserve.

123
00:08:47,797 --> 00:08:49,632
Yes, sir. It is.

124
00:08:50,383 --> 00:08:53,136
- But...
- My colleagues are all Seminole Indians.

125
00:08:53,303 --> 00:08:55,597
Did I mention that?
You're familiar, I'm sure...

126
00:08:55,764 --> 00:08:58,224
...with the State of Florida
v. James E. Billie?

127
00:08:58,725 --> 00:09:03,521
So you know that even though Seminole
Chief Billie killed a Florida panther...

128
00:09:03,688 --> 00:09:05,815
...one of what, 40 in the entire world?

129
00:09:05,982 --> 00:09:07,317
- Forty.
- Forty.

130
00:09:07,484 --> 00:09:09,903
The state couldn't successfully
prosecute him...

131
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:12,947
...because, you know, he's an Indian,
and it's his right.

132
00:09:13,114 --> 00:09:18,161
As repugnant as you and I, as white
conservationists, might find his actions.

133
00:09:18,328 --> 00:09:21,122
- But...
- Not to mention the failed attempts...

134
00:09:21,289 --> 00:09:25,710
...on three occasions to prosecute
Seminoles for poaching palm fronds.

135
00:09:25,877 --> 00:09:31,132
Which I believe they use to thatch
the roofs of their traditional chickee huts.

136
00:09:31,675 --> 00:09:34,135
How about that?
With the chickee huts, right?

137
00:09:34,302 --> 00:09:38,390
Yeah, he's right. That's exactly what
we use them for. Chickee huts.

138
00:09:42,977 --> 00:09:44,938
Yeah, but I don't...

139
00:09:45,105 --> 00:09:48,441
I can't let you fellas leave yet.

140
00:09:49,317 --> 00:09:52,779
- Just hold on there a minute.
- Okay.

141
00:09:54,614 --> 00:09:56,991
Charles, is that you?

142
00:09:58,952 --> 00:10:00,787
Did you eat lunch?

143
00:10:01,413 --> 00:10:05,291
I had that shrimp cocktail in the fridge.
Was it yours?

144
00:10:05,458 --> 00:10:08,795
I hope not. I couldn't remember,
so I ate it.

145
00:10:08,962 --> 00:10:12,090
Maybe we should write our names
on our food items from now on.

146
00:10:12,257 --> 00:10:14,759
- What's with you?
- My back.

147
00:10:14,968 --> 00:10:19,347
Charles, you'll be glad. I have a plan
to get me out of your house, pronto.

148
00:10:19,514 --> 00:10:24,310
- A job is a plan. Is your plan a job?
- Drum roll, please.

149
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:28,815
I'm gonna be a screenwriter.
Like you.

150
00:10:28,982 --> 00:10:31,901
I know you think this is just
one of my "get rich quick" schemes...

151
00:10:32,068 --> 00:10:33,695
...but I'm doing it right this time.

152
00:10:33,862 --> 00:10:37,657
I'm taking a three-day seminar,
and it's only 500 bucks.

153
00:10:37,824 --> 00:10:40,368
Screenwriting seminars are bullshit.

154
00:10:40,535 --> 00:10:43,538
In theory, I agree with you.
But this one's different.

155
00:10:43,705 --> 00:10:45,665
This one's highly regarded
in the industry.

156
00:10:45,832 --> 00:10:48,084
Donald, don't say "industry."

157
00:10:48,251 --> 00:10:50,211
I'm sorry. I forgot.

158
00:10:50,378 --> 00:10:52,964
Charles, this guy knows screenwriting.

159
00:10:53,131 --> 00:10:55,508
People come from all over
to study with him.

160
00:10:55,675 --> 00:10:58,345
- I'll pay you back as soon as l...
- Let me explain something.

161
00:10:58,511 --> 00:11:02,182
Anybody who says he's got "the answer"
is going to attract desperate people...

162
00:11:02,349 --> 00:11:03,975
...be it in the world of religion...

163
00:11:04,142 --> 00:11:06,519
I just need to lie down
while you explain this to me.

164
00:11:06,686 --> 00:11:08,813
Sorry. I apologize.

165
00:11:09,606 --> 00:11:11,399
Okay, go ahead.

166
00:11:11,566 --> 00:11:14,027
- So...
- Sorry. Okay. Go.

167
00:11:14,194 --> 00:11:15,528
There are no rules, Donald.

168
00:11:15,695 --> 00:11:18,156
And anybody who says there are
is just, you know...

169
00:11:18,365 --> 00:11:21,409
Not rules. Principles.

170
00:11:22,035 --> 00:11:25,872
McKee writes that a rule says,
"You must do it this way."

171
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:30,669
A principle says, "This works
and has through all remembered time."

172
00:11:30,835 --> 00:11:33,838
The script I'm starting,
it's about flowers.

173
00:11:34,714 --> 00:11:37,050
Nobody's ever done a movie
about flowers before.

174
00:11:37,217 --> 00:11:41,054
- So there are no guidelines.
- What about Flowers for Algernon?

175
00:11:41,221 --> 00:11:43,890
Well, that's not about flowers.
And it's not a movie.

176
00:11:44,057 --> 00:11:45,975
I'm sorry. I never saw it.

177
00:11:46,142 --> 00:11:47,560
How...? Okay, keep going.

178
00:11:47,727 --> 00:11:50,355
Look, my point is
that those teachers are dangerous...

179
00:11:50,522 --> 00:11:52,524
...if your goal is to try
to do something new.

180
00:11:52,691 --> 00:11:56,444
A writer should always have that goal.
Writing is a journey into the unknown.

181
00:11:56,611 --> 00:11:59,906
It's not building, you know,
one of your model airplanes.

182
00:12:04,411 --> 00:12:06,913
McKee is a former Fulbright Scholar,
Charles.

183
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:10,208
Are you a former Fulbright Scholar?

184
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:16,589
Say something. I dragged her here,
and now I'm not saying anything.

185
00:12:16,756 --> 00:12:18,591
Make her laugh.
Say something funny.

186
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:22,387
I hate parties, Amelia.
Why did we come here?

187
00:12:22,595 --> 00:12:25,265
Because we're hip, young trendsetters
on the make, aren't we?

188
00:12:25,432 --> 00:12:28,226
More like old losers
sitting on the floor, maybe.

189
00:12:28,393 --> 00:12:33,189
Jesus, Charlie. Speak for yourself.
Okay...

190
00:12:34,357 --> 00:12:36,443
Charlie, we're gonna fix you up.

191
00:12:36,609 --> 00:12:40,989
We're gonna solve the whole Charlie
Kaufman mess for once and for all.

192
00:12:41,156 --> 00:12:42,866
- Okay.
- Okay, let me see.

193
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:46,453
What do you need?
What, what, what?

194
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,497
Well, I'm glad you took
the orchid script.

195
00:12:49,789 --> 00:12:53,084
I think it will be good for you
to get out of your head.

196
00:12:53,251 --> 00:12:57,547
I think it'll ground you to think about the
bigger picture, about nature and stuff.

197
00:12:57,797 --> 00:13:00,633
I still can't believe they gave me
that job.

198
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:04,679
I mean, after that lunch.
I was sweating insanely.

199
00:13:04,846 --> 00:13:07,724
I was ranting. I was a mess.

200
00:13:07,891 --> 00:13:09,893
You were just nervous
because she was pretty.

201
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,853
How do you know she was pretty?

202
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:15,899
After eight months of knowing you,
I think I get what makes you sweat.

203
00:13:16,858 --> 00:13:19,819
Well, whatever.
Well, moving on, what next?

204
00:13:19,986 --> 00:13:23,490
You need a new getup.
This whole flannel shirt thing...

205
00:13:23,656 --> 00:13:27,243
...it's not really doing anything
for you anymore.

206
00:13:30,288 --> 00:13:33,083
Thanks for coming out
with me tonight, Amelia.

207
00:13:49,182 --> 00:13:51,017
To begin.

208
00:13:51,184 --> 00:13:52,519
To begin.

209
00:13:53,144 --> 00:13:54,938
How to start?

210
